<subSubSection id="C31888CFFFE1562BFEB2D0DCF94000E4" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="28" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="key">
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D0DCF933060F" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D0DCF933066F" blockId="3.[265,1368,204,286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D0DCF933066F" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
1 Scutellum laterally setulose, dorsally glossy without pubescence; intermediate scutellar bristle much shorter than basal scutellar bristle; wing markings as in 
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFD29D116FEB5066F" box="[658,734,262,286]" captionStart="Figures 52, 53" captionStartId="28.[204,275,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[206,1338,208,1196]" captionTargetId="figure-9@28.[204,1338,198,1196]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 52, 53.(52) Bama papuanum (Hennig), distal part of aedeagus.Scale = 0.2 mm.(53) BamashinonagaiMcAlpine, left wing of holotype, male.bu, bulb;g, glans;lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, lobe of preglans;st, stipe;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684920/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE1562CFBD4D116F933066F" authority="McAlpine" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" box="[1135,1368,262,286]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shinonagai">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFE1562CFBD4D116F88D066F" box="[1135,1254,262,286]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">shinonagai</emphasis>
McAlpine
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D13CF933060F" blockId="3.[265,1368,300,382]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D13CF933060F" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Scutellum without setulae, its dorsal surface with covering of minute erect pubescence; intermediate scutellar bristle c. as long as basal scutellar bristle; wing markings otherwise .................................................................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D18EF9330542" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D18EF9330680" blockId="3.[265,1368,414,497]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D18EF9330680" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
2 Marginal and submarginal cells of wing entirely dark brown to black, or (in male) first posterior cell with spotted pattern (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFED0D1C9FDD20680" box="[363,441,473,497]" captionStart="Figures 23–26" captionStartId="16.[357,429,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[357,1186,151,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-9@16.[357,1186,151,1668]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 23–26. Bama gressitti n.sp. (23) Left wing of male. (24) Left wing of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) ..................................................................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D1EFF9330542" blockId="3.[265,1368,510,564]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D1EFF9330542" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Marginal and submarginal cells with hyaline to pale yellowish zones; first posterior cell without such pattern .......................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D244F9330477" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D244F93305D7" blockId="3.[265,1368,595,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D244F93305D7" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
3 Vein 5 on distal part of discal cell surrounded by pale brown zone; discal crossvein almost straight; palpus dark grey-brown; 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFE1562CFED8D29FFD1C05D7" box="[355,375,655,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
only: first posterior cell with complex spotted pattern (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFC15D29EFF9305D7" box="[942,1016,654,678]" captionStart="Figures 23–26" captionStartId="16.[357,429,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[357,1186,151,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-9@16.[357,1186,151,1668]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figures 23–26. Bama gressitti n.sp. (23) Left wing of male. (24) Left wing of female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684893/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) ............................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE1562CFB72D29FF97405D7" authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1225,1311,655,678]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gressitti" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFE1562CFB72D29FF97405D7" box="[1225,1311,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">gressitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A245BA2DFFE1562CFA9DD29FF93305D7" box="[1318,1368,655,678]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D2A4F9330477" blockId="3.[265,1368,691,774]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D2A4F9330477" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
—— Vein 5 on discal cell not clouded with brown; discal crossvein curved; palpus variable in colour; 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFE1562CFD65D2C1FE990599" box="[734,754,721,744]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
only: first posterior cell without spotted pattern (so far as known) ................................................................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D336F9330362" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D336F93304E7" blockId="3.[265,1368,806,918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D336F93304E7" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
4 Vein 2 with abrupt flexure just before level of anterior crossvein (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFED0D354FDC1042D" box="[363,426,836,860]" captionStart="Figures 7–10" captionStartId="9.[166,238,1172,1194]" captionTargetBox="[167,1466,211,1127]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[167,1467,201,1157]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 7–10. Bama flexifer n.sp., holotype male. (7) Head. (8) Left wing. (9) Distal part of aedeagus, scale = 0.3 mm. (10) Right arista (basal segmentation unclear).bu, bulb;fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, preglans;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684877/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); dark mark enclosing discal crossvein broadly confluent with dark costal zone; prescutellar acrostichal bristle present; arista uniformly short-haired, with simple apex (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFCD3D36EFFDE04E7" box="[872,949,894,918]" captionStart="Figures 7–10" captionStartId="9.[166,238,1172,1194]" captionTargetBox="[167,1466,211,1127]" captionTargetId="figure-9@9.[167,1467,201,1157]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 7–10. Bama flexifer n.sp., holotype male. (7) Head. (8) Left wing. (9) Distal part of aedeagus, scale = 0.3 mm. (10) Right arista (basal segmentation unclear).bu, bulb;fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans; lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, preglans;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684877/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) ....................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE1562CFB6ED36EF97404E7" authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1237,1311,894,918]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexifer" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFE1562CFB6ED36EF97404E7" box="[1237,1311,894,918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">flexifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A245BA2DFFE1562CFA9DD36FF93304E7" box="[1318,1368,895,918]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D3B4F9330362" blockId="3.[265,1368,932,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D3B4F9330362" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
—— Vein 2 with moderate curvature only (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFD48D3B4FF2A04CD" box="[755,833,932,956]" captionStart="Figures 17–20" captionStartId="13.[166,238,1744,1766]" captionTargetBox="[186,1444,160,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-9@13.[166,1466,151,1729]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 17–20. Bama signifer n.sp., holotype female. (17) Left wing. (18) Right mid coxa, anteroventral view. (19) Distal half of left arista, scale = 0.2 mm. (20) Dorsal view of abdomen, sclerites outlined only." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684887/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); discal crossvein not enclosed in brown mark; prescutellar acrostichal bristle absent; arista bare on most of length, with lanceolate subapical palette (at least in female; 
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFDC6D3ECFEA20365" box="[637,713,1020,1044]" captionStart="Figures 17–20" captionStartId="13.[166,238,1744,1766]" captionTargetBox="[186,1444,160,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-9@13.[166,1466,151,1729]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figures 17–20. Bama signifer n.sp., holotype female. (17) Left wing. (18) Right mid coxa, anteroventral view. (19) Distal half of left arista, scale = 0.2 mm. (20) Dorsal view of abdomen, sclerites outlined only." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684887" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684887/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) ......................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE1562CFB75D3ECF9740365" authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1230,1311,1020,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signifer" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFE1562CFB75D3ECF9740365" box="[1230,1311,1020,1044]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A245BA2DFFE1562CFA9DD3ECF9330362" box="[1318,1368,1020,1043]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D423F9330397" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D423F93303D5" blockId="3.[265,1368,1075,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D423F93303D5" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
5 Anal crossvein subangularly bent near mid-length; wing markings approximately as in 
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFD11D441FE820318" box="[682,745,1105,1129]" captionStart="Figures 1, 2" captionStartId="5.[249,321,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[249,1366,168,970]" captionTargetId="figure-260@5.[249,1383,149,982]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 1, 2. Bama bipunctatum (Hendel). (1) Left wing of male, Sirinumu Dam. (2) Distal part of aedeagus, Sirinumu Dam, scale = 0.1 mm.bu, bulb; fs, flexible section of aedeagus; g, glans;lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, preglans;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684867/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, but sometimes stigmatal brown band fading posteriorly; fore femur entirely brown; hind femur yellow ............................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE1562CFBD6D49CF93303D5" authority="(Hendel)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" box="[1133,1368,1164,1188]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctatum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFE1562CFBD6D49CF89903D5" box="[1133,1266,1164,1188]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">bipunctatum</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D4A1F9330397" blockId="3.[265,1368,1201,1254]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D4A1F9330397" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Anal crossvein most strongly bent or curved on anterior part; wing markings diverse; coloration of femora diverse ............................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D516F93302ED" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D516F9330229" blockId="3.[265,1368,1286,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D516F9330229" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">6 Capitellum of halter dark brown to black; apical part of first posterior cell largely hyaline, but with very narrow apical marginal brown line .................................................................................................................. 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D577F93302ED" blockId="3.[265,1368,1382,1436]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D577F93302ED" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">—— Capitellum of halter white or yellow; apical part of first posterior cell variable, but often partly brown .......................................................................... 8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE1562CFEB2D5ACF9330142" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D5ACF9330281" blockId="3.[265,1368,1468,1521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE1562CFEB2D5ACF9330281" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
7 Distal parts of veins 3 and 4 almost straight, markedly diverging to apex; wing markings as in 
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE1562CFD26D5C9FEB00280" box="[669,731,1497,1521]" captionStart="Figures 3, 4" captionStartId="6.[352,424,1977,1999]" captionTargetBox="[204,1338,1276,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-603@6.[204,1338,1276,1961]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 3, 4. Bama divergens n.sp., male. (3) Left wing. (4) Right hind tibia and tarsus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684871" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684871/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
(male) ......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE1562CFB0CD5C9F9740280" authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1207,1311,1497,1521]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFE1562CFB0CD5C9F9740280" box="[1207,1311,1497,1521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A245BA2DFFE1562CFA9DD5C9F9330281" box="[1318,1368,1497,1520]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE1562CFEB2D5EFF9330142" blockId="3.[265,1368,1534,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="27">
