<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE6562BFE86D105FDFA065C" box="[317,401,277,301]" captionStart="Figures 33, 34" captionStartId="20.[356,428,1192,1214]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,151,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-9@20.[204,1338,151,1179]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 33, 34. Bama grande n.sp., holotype female. (33) Right wing. (34) Mid coxae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684901/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Figs 34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE6562BFE26D105FDD0065C" box="[413,443,277,301]" captionStart="Figures 37, 38" captionStartId="22.[259,331,1610,1632]" captionTargetBox="[259,1283,151,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-189@22.[259,1283,151,1601]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figures 37, 38. Bama martini n.sp., holotype female. (37) First costal cell and adjacent region of left wing," figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684907/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">38</figureCitation>
); posteroventral angle of sternopleuron (near mid coxa) with some black setulae ................................................................................................. 11
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE6562BFF60D17AF9400526" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
