<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE6562BFE0AD215FD96056C" box="[433,509,517,541]" captionStart="Figures 33, 34" captionStartId="20.[356,428,1192,1214]" captionTargetBox="[231,1337,151,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-9@20.[204,1338,151,1179]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figures 33, 34. Bama grande n.sp., holotype female. (33) Right wing. (34) Mid coxae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684901/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); base of submarginal cell hyaline; first costal cell bare except near distal extremity; discal crossvein more than twice as long as anterior crossvein .................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE6562BFB1DD22FF8990526" authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1190,1266,575,599]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grande" status="n.sp.">
