<keyLead id="30F37871FFE6562BFF60D3BBF9400491" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">—— Penultimate section of vein 4 much shorter than discal crossvein; wing markings otherwise ........................................................................................................ 14</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F6C3E1FFE6562BFF60D410F94002EC" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFE6562BFF60D410F9400395" blockId="4.[219,1323,1023,1253]" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
<keyLead id="30F37871FFE6562BFF60D410F9400395" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">
14 Fore femur yellow basally, brown distally; first basal cell with brown to blackish transverse mark (smaller in male) c. halfway between basal and anterior crossveins; second section of vein 4 almost straight; penultimate section of vein 4 not shorter than anterior crossvein; distomedial lobe of mid coxa prominent but broadly rounded, setulose, but without single isolated spinescent bristle (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFE6562BFDB9D4BFFE3F03B9" box="[514,596,1199,1224]" captionStart="Figures 27–29" captionStartId="18.[289,361,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[289,1254,151,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-9@18.[289,1254,151,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figures 27–29. Bama bickeli n.sp. (27) Left wing of holotype male. (28) Left wing of female. (29) Mid coxae and adjacent parts of female, anteroventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684897/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="28">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); male: hind basitarsus broadened, compressed ............................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFE6562BFB10D4DDF8990394" authority="McAlpine, 2015" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1195,1266,1229,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickeli" status="n.sp.">
